data.enText: if a person or their skin tans or is tanned , they become brown as a result of spending time in the sun
to make animal skin into leather by treating it with chemicals

data.chText: 晒成棕褐肤色；晒成的棕褐色
data.enText: the brown colour that sb with pale skin goes when they have been in the sun

tr: a light brown the color of topaz
ratio of the opposite to the adjacent side of a right-angled triangle
a browning of the skin resulting from exposure to the rays of the sun
get a tan, from wind or sun
treat skins and hides with tannic acid so as to convert them into leather

value.def: If you have a tan, your skin has become darker than usual because you have been in the sun.

example.ex: She is tall and blonde, with a permanent tan.
example.tran: 她高个儿，一头金发，皮肤黝黑。

value.def: If a part of your body tans or if you tan it, your skin becomes darker than usual because you spend a lot of time in the sun.

example.ex: I have very pale skin that never tans...
example.tran: 我皮肤很白，怎么也晒不黑。

example.ex: Leigh rolled over on her stomach to tan her back.
example.tran: 莉翻了个身趴下，开始晒后背。

example.ex: Their skin was tanned and glowing from their weeks at the sea.
example.tran: 他们在海边呆了几个星期，皮肤晒得黝黑发亮。

value.def: Something that is tan is a light brown colour.
To tan animal skins means to make them into leather by treating them with tannin or other chemicals.

trans: 苦黑啤酒(苦啤酒和黑啤酒混合)
